`.lit` is the culmination of a few seemingly[^1] disperate ideas: [[Literate Programming]], [[Interactive Notebooks]], [[Digital Gardens]] and [[Wiki]].

Meant to enable [[Guided Learning]] ‚Äî where the author shows the reader by *tactile* example ‚Äî and exploration or [[Rapid Prototyping]] while trying not to be a separate system from which a student or project *graduates* but which is an *acceptable[^2] development evironment* for professional engineers.

[^1]: Although not really
[^2]: This inevitably involves trade-offs, but `.lit` aims to be explicit about them and provide a path/route to either edit source files outside of the `.lit` UI, or execute code as normal from the `terminal/cli`.
